
Welcome to ShockForce!

Hit <help_screen> for a complete help list.
There is not yet a manual available.
Hit F2 to change your view (cockpit, follow, and outside).
Hit f3 to toggle between short range and long range radar and map.

Use <general_tank_movement> to move your tank.
Hit <autocannon_fire> to fire your autocannon.
Use <lower_jet_strength> and <raise_jet_strength> to lower and raise your altitude.
Land by lowering the jet strength to zero.
Also, when you are landed you will be cloaked from enemy detection from far range.
Raise your jet strength when you want to move.
Holding down <shift> makes the tank accelerate at the maximum rate.

Use <target_under_reticle> to target object under your reticle.
Load up on special weapons by landing on one of your fuel units.
Hit <target_closest_fuel> to target the closest fuel pad.
Repair a damaged hovertank on one of your repair units.
Hit <target_closest_repair> to target the closest repair pad.
Hit <target_tank> to target the closest enemy tank.
Hit <cycle_target> to cycle through enemy tanks once you have targeted one.

Hit "i" to target incomming missiles.
You can store targets into your tanks memory with ctrl+F5-8 keys.
You can recall a stored target by hitting the F5-F8 key that you stored it on. 

Remember, tanks of your own color are friendly -- don't shoot them.
You will take damage if you fire on friendly units or tanks.
Hit <weapon_keys> to fire any of the special weapons (you must have them).
On tanks, pulse shells (default key 1 or right mouse button) have a range of aprox. 1100m.
On scouts, 1 key or right mouse will fire your repair beam.
This can repair friendly units, or damage and steal energy from enemy units.

Use Insert and Delete to zoom in and out while aiming.
Shift+Insert or Shift+Delete will zoom in max and zoom out max.
Zooming in and firing Pulse shells is a good method of sniping enemies.
Piercer missiles (key 2) are semi-guided armor-piercing weapons.
Thumper missiles (key 3) are semi-guided concussion weapons that disorient targets.
Hunter missiles (key 4) are guided weapons with extremely long range.
All missiles need a target to be effective.
Use TAB to cycle through targets in your field of view...
Or use <target_under_reticle> to target under reticle...
Or use <target_tank> to target the nearest enemy tank.
Use ` (back-tick) to clear current target.
Caltrops (key 5) are short-lived heat-seeking bombs that track tanks within 200m.
Mines (key 6) are powerful permanent devices that are only triggered by enemies.


Hit <map_overview> to look at the big game map.
Press N to cycle through satellite, altitude, and slope maps.

You can build or extend your base by picking up and installing cargo.
Press C to target the nearest friendly cargo.
Pickup cargo boxes by touching them.
Hit <cargo_drop> to drop a cargo box that you are carrying.
Hit <cargo_deploy> to deploy the contents your cargo box.
You can only carry one cargo box at a time.
Most installations need to be in range (300m) of a Power Cell to function.
Fuel pads supply fuel and weapons to friendly tanks when landed on.
Repair pads fix damaged tanks when landed on and allow new tanks to respawn.
Sentry cannons fire automatically at incoming enemies and missiles in mid range.
Gun turrets fire autocannons at enemy units within 400m.
Missile launchers fire missiles at ememy units within a fairly long range.
Target any defensive unit to view it's range on the radar and map.
Darklights block enemy radar detection (but not enemy targetting).
Skypumps are used to power starships.

Hit <start_message> to send a message.
Enter a / before your message to send it to a specific group.
/t sends a message just to your team.
/a sends a message to all players.
/NAME sends a message to the named player.
Entering two slashes (//) will make the channel your default from now on.
For instance, //t will make TEAM your default channel.

Tanks cannot damage starships by themselves.
Starships will attack each other, but they are evenly matched.
If the enemy has more ships than you in adjacent squares, they will overwhelm your ships.
Your ships will send you distress signals when they are being overpowered.
Your team must move then to a powered square to save them from destruction,
or must move in another ship to even up the balance of ships between teams.
Starships will drop cargo that you can pick up and deploy.

If you have picked up and installed the UPLINK, you control your team's ships.
Install the uplink by hitting the "." key.
Uninstall the uplink by hitting the "," key.
If you have the uplink, you can issue orders to the ships by doing the following.
Hit "m" to bring up the map mode, and then click on the uplink tab on the top left button.
Click on a starship and a menu of orders, and what is in their order queue will appear.
Use the menus to issue the orders that you want to give your ships.
Orbital bombardment will bomb all enemy units in the square below the ship.
If there are no enemy units when the bombing is to begin, it will abort.
Read the included manual for more info on starship control.

Skypumps provide power for starships.
One skypump in a sector will let a ship move into that area (the square will be lit).
Two skypumps in a sector will allow a new ship to warp in (the square will be lit brightly).
When warp glimpse occurs, a green cloud appears in the sky,
and a warp symbol will appear in that square on the map.
After this, a countdown to warp push begins.
If there are still two skypumps active when warp push occurs, a new starship warps in.
Starships can also bombard the sector they're in, destroying all enemy units.
A team may only have a maximum of three starships at a time.

Remember, your goal is to destroy the enemy bases. 
As long as the foe has at least one active Repair Pad, destroyed tanks can respawn.
Defend your own bases with sentry cannons and tanks.
Use the strategic map <map_overview> to plan attacks. 

	
To turn off online help, hit ESC and reduce help level to zero in Options.
Remember, report any bugs or suggestions to bolt@bolt-action.com!





